Leaders of the Communist Party of China (CPC) on Thursday stressed the importance of safeguarding drug safety and vowed severe punishment for violations.Members of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee held a meeting to hear a report on the investigation into the case of illegal production of rabies vaccines by Changchun Changsheng Life Sciences Limited that has become a national scandal.The meeting urged a quickening of improvements in drug safety supervision with provisions for strict legal penalties. It also agreed on punitive measures for officials implicated in the scandal, including the removal of Jin Yuhui, vice governor of Jilin Province, where the company is located. Backgrounder: the AIIB explainedImpact of anti-corruption campaignBig changes in China's top military brass Protecting peace, stability is top of human rights agenda for XinjiangWhy Washington stabs Turkey in the backScientists create lightweight, fire-retardant artificial wood Antibiotic misuse becoming worldwide growing concernFirefighters gain on blazes Demonstration How To Say Love To A Chinese Girl

